ABSTRACT
The Advanced Library System is a web-based application designed to efficiently manage a small-scale digital book catalog. The system allows users to add, edit, delete, and search books dynamically while maintaining a storage limit. The project focuses on usability, responsiveness, and modern UI design using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
The system utilizes browser local storage for persistent data handling without requiring a backend server. It ensures a smooth user experience through interactive UI elements and real-time search functionality. This project demonstrates the practical implementation of front-end technologies in building functional and user-friendly applications.
Keywords: Library System, Web Development, Local Storage, JavaScript, UI/UX

