CHAPTER 1: BACKGROUND AND TECHNICAL OVERVIEW
The increasing need for efficient management of books has led to the development of digital library systems. Traditional systems are often manual and inefficient. The Advanced Library System provides a lightweight, browser-based solution.
Technologies Used:
•	HTML for structure
•	CSS for styling and responsive UI
•	JavaScript for functionality
•	Local Storage for data persistence
________________________________________
CHAPTER 2: PROBLEM STATEMENT AND MOTIVATION
Managing books manually can lead to data loss, inefficiency, and lack of organization. The motivation behind this project is to create a simple yet efficient system that allows users to manage a limited set of books digitally.
________________________________________
CHAPTER 3: NOVELTY AND INNOVATIVE CONTRIBUTIONS
