•	Local storage-based persistence without backend
•	Capacity-limited system for controlled data handling
________________________________________
CHAPTER 4: TECHNICAL ADVANTAGES AND PRACTICAL USEFULNESS
•	Easy to use and interactive interface
•	No server required
•	Lightweight and fast performance
•	Cross-platform compatibility
________________________________________
CHAPTER 5: DETAILED METHODOLOGY / SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE
The system consists of three main modules:
1.	Input Module: Accepts book details (title, author, category)
2.	Processing Module: Handles add, edit, delete, and search operations
3.	Storage Module: Uses localStorage to store data
Workflow:
User Input → JavaScript Processing → Local Storage → Display Output
________________________________________
CHAPTER 6: PRIOR ART AND RELATED WORK
Existing library systems often require databases and backend frameworks. This project differs by implementing a frontend-only solution using browser storage.
